questionTemplates.text:
W: Professor Smith caught some students cheating on the mid-term exam and failed them.
M: Serves them right.
{a}

W: It's too late for me to catch a bus.
M: You'd better take a taxi.
{a}

W: Adam. I can see that you simply couldn't give up smoking.
M: Nonsense. Smoking is the easiest thing in the world to give up. I've done it a hundred times.
{a}

M: The bus is always late.
W: I know. I've been waiting for it for half an hour. If it doesn't come in another 15 minutes, I'll go on foot.
{a}

W: The morning paper says the space shuttle is taking off at 10 a.m. tomorrow.
M: Yeah, it's just another one of this year's routine missions. The first mission was undertaken a decade ago and broadcast live then worldwide.
{a}

W: Is there anything I can do for you? Do you want to borrow some books?
M: No, I'd like to get a library card. This is my student card.
{a}

M: If you'd like to go there for dinner this evening, I'll phone the restaurant and reserve another place.
W: Thank you, but I promised my sister I'd take her to the airport.
{a}

F: Would you please take care of my cat while I'm away?
M: With pleasure.
{a}

M: I want to invite the Johnson's to the party. Do you know their address?
W: No, but I'd rather they didn't come. I think their coming will bother you.
{a}

W: Did you use credit cards on your vacation last month in Europe?
M: Sure I did. They certainly beat going around with a wallet full of big bills. But carrying lots of cash is still very common among some older people traveling abroad.
{a}

W: Oh man, what's wrong with your eyes? Did you get into a fight?
M: Oh, do they look terrible? I stayed up all night to do homework.
{a}

M: Are you going to put the seeds of tomatoes into the soil, too?
W: I think there is plenty of space to the right of the cucumbers.
{a}

M: Look at your hair?
W: A big wind outside.
{a}

M: Do you have any idea what the passage is about?
W: I'm as much in the dark as you are.
{a}

W: Where is Yang Pei?
M: He is helping the farmers pick oranges. The farmers are always busy in this season.
{a}

W: What did you do on the beach?
M: You know, I made sand castles, that sort of things, and hunted for shells.
{a}

M: Are you moving into a new house? Need a hand with those boxes?
W: That's okay, I can manage. They look big, but aren't very heavy actually.
{a}

W: Can you describe what you do?
M: I wash office building windows. I go high up in the basket to reach the windows.
{a}

Woman: Are you looking forward to going home?
Man: Not exactly. The climate here really agrees with me.
{a}

M: Excuse me. Where can I find the manager in this building? I need to speak to him right now.
W: Sorry. I can't help you. I'm not familiar with this building. My friend lives here.
{a}

W: I thought there was still time for me to apply for a student loan. But someone just told me that the closing date was last Tuesday.
M: Are you sure? I thought we still had another month. Wait, I've got a brochure right here. Last Tuesday was the opening date.
{a}

W: Dad, Christmas is coming. Could you give me some money? I want to buy a card for my friend Mary. It has been two months since she was in my school.
M: Oh dear, how thoughtful you are!
{a}

M: The visiting economist is speaking tonight, but Dr. Johnson doesn't seem to think much of him.
W: That's because Dr. Johnson comes from an entirely different school of thought.
{a}

F: Where did you find your dictionary?
M: I found it under my bed.
{a}

M: How much is the shirt?
W: One hundred and twenty yuan, but there is a 50% off in price.
{a}

M: What do you think of the film we saw last night?
W: Well, I don't like it at all, but my sister said it was a fantastic one and she would go and see it again.
{a}
